---
// src/pages/squeaky-greyhound.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = "Squeaky and Greyhound";
const publishDate = "April 10, 2023";
---
<Layout title={`${title} - Project`}>
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <article class="glass p-12 rounded-3xl max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Project Header -->
      <header class="mb-8">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-2">{title}</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-200 text-lg">Published on {publishDate}</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Project Content -->
      <section class="prose max-w-none text-gray-200">
        <p>
          Servo Squeaky is a 3D printed, open-source quadruped robot developed by the Terrestrial Robotics Engineering and Controls at Virginia Tech. It features a servo-based powertrain that enables high-fidelity walking and crawling.
        </p>
        <p>
          Initially, I redesigned some of Servo Squeaky's mechanical components to make it operational. A video demonstration shows the improved version with a custom inverse kinematics algorithm programmed onto a Teensy microcontroller.
        </p>
        <p>
          Once the robot was functional, it was handed off to the high-level software team for advanced algorithms. I then focused on creating a new version, dubbed Greyhound, with enhanced mobilityâ€”enabling running and jumping.
        </p>
        <p>
          Greyhound conceals brushless DC motors and 3D printed gearboxes within its legs. A demonstration of the PID control system and the low-level inverse kinematics converting end-effector positions to motor commands is shown below.
        </p>

        <!-- Embedded YouTube Video -->
        <div class="video-container my-8">
            <iframe 
            width="560" 
            height="315" 
            src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/SC4uWbzgVt0" 
            title="YouTube video player" 
            frameborder="0" 
            allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" 
            allowfullscreen 
            class="rounded-2xl w-full">
            </iframe>
        </div>        
        
        <!-- Project Images -->
        <figure class="my-8">
          <img src="/squeaky-greyhound-1.png" alt="Squeaky and Greyhound - Image 1" class="rounded-2xl w-full" />
          <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">
            Design implementation and results.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-8">
          <figure>
            <img src="/squeaky-greyhound-2.png" alt="Squeaky and Greyhound - Image 2" class="rounded-2xl w-full" />
            <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">
              System communication diagram.
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
          <figure>
            <img src="/squeaky-greyhound-3.png" alt="Squeaky and Greyhound - Image 3" class="rounded-2xl w-full" />
            <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">
              Mechanical design goals and implementation
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
